@Node ENGLISH "ScanHTML.guide/About English"

@{jcenter}@{u}@{b}A word or two about English@{ub}@{uu}

@{jleft}My primary language is French.  I read English very well but I'm sure what I write is awful.  Sorry about that.

I could write this in French but maybe @{b}you@{ub} could not read it!

When I will have some free time I will write the docs in French too but that's not now!

@EndNode

@Node INTRODUCTION "ScanHTML.guide/Introduction"

@{jcenter}@{u}@{b}Introduction@{ub}@{uu}

@{jleft}I'm writing ScanHTML because I want to build an HTTP robot.

An HTTP robot is a program that can automatically download one or more files using HTTP.  Then it can scan those files to search for references to other files that it download upon some conditions and so on...

ScanHTML scans HTML files and creates a list of urls. That's all!

@EndNode

@Node FEATURES "ScanHTML.guide/Features"

@{jcenter}@{u}@{b}Features@{ub}@{uu}
@{jleft}@{lindent 4}@{pari -2}
@{par}- Written in C, which means QUICK compared with ARexx scripts
@{par}- Can append to or overwrite an existing url list
@{par}- Can complete relative URLs (".", "..", & "/" are understood)
@{par}- Accepts @{b}two@{ub} independant AmigaDOS patterns to select which URLs to keep
@{par}- Select which type(s) of URLs to keep (backgrounds, images, references)

@{pard}@{lindent 0}
Not a very long list but, there IS a list! :)

@EndNode

